<h4>Layers</h4>
<br />
<p>The application works with the concept of layers. It is then possible to overlay tiles.</p>
<p>The draw function is by default enabled by selecting the layer.</p>
<p>The erase function is enabled if the user wants to delete the tiles from the layer one by one.</p>
<p>The clear all function clears all the tiles in that layer.</p>
<p>The preview function hides the display of the tiles of that layer.</p>
<hr />
<h4>Selection of Tiles</h4>
<br />
<p>
	The selection of Tiles is performed using the mouse. 
	With the left mouse button select a Tile.
	<br/>
	You can also select multiple tiles using the left mouse button and dragging.
</p>
<hr />
<h4>Reference Element</h4>
<br />
<p>
	It is mandatory to include the reference element. 
	This will be the starting point / direction of the navigation in the environment.
</p>
<hr />
<h4>Canvas</h4>
<br />
<p>You can resize the canvas on the Edit menu. </p>
<p>
	By default a screen size of 25x15 tiles is generated.
	<br/>
	Each square of the screen has an approximate scale of 50cm x 50cm in the real world.
</p>